    <note>Huang(2) Muzhi [15455] Muzhi moved to the family residence of his mother, Cishan's [15449] first wife (born Li) in Fuliang where the Li lineage head (zuzhang) was Li(2) Chunnian [983] (q.v.). Although he is identified as a Fengcheng Huang, Muzhi was buried in Linchuan. His son, Shaozong [15458], is also listed as a Fengcheng Huang as is his probably brother Yuanzhi [15456] in the Nanchang FZ. Yuanzhi is also listed as a Hongzhou, Fengxin county resident in Jiangxi TZ, 22.8a. Shaozong is also listed as a Fengcheng resident in Jiangxi TZ, 22.24b, but his elder brother, Luan [15457], is listed as a Linchuan jinshi in Jiangxi TZ, 22.26b. I am therefore going to consider them all as Linchuan residents, who moved to the respective addresses of their jinshi. Zhou Bida, WJ, 78.11a-15a. CBD, 4, 2902.</note>
